Reasoning: The paper discusses database analytics algorithms and their effectiveness over different structural organizations of data. This topic falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves using algorithms to predict relationships and concepts. The paper also discusses the fundamental properties of data analytics algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the representation independence of algorithms, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) as it involves analyzing the security of algorithms under different representations.
